# -*- coding:UTF-8 -*-

"""
compatible Python: 3.6.4

Author: Andrew YE

Date: 2018-01-24

Topic: variable 变量

Content:
    1. variable name element: alphabet character, underscore character, number
    2. naming rule: a. only class name need the first capital letter for every single word;
                    b. constant need full capital letters;
                    c. other object only need low-case letters for every single word
                    d. variable name can't begin with a number
                    e. variable name is case-sensitive, spam, Spam, SPAM, sPaM are four different variables
                    f. camelcase is more better than underscores for naming variables although this's against
                       the Python PEP 8


"""

# file name: full low-case letters
# --> templatetest.py or template_test.py
# package: full low-case letters
# --> templatepackage or template_package
# module: full low-case letters
# --> templatemodule, no underscore
# class: the first capital letter
# --> TemplateClass, underscore only for inner class
# functions: full low-case letters
# --> templatefunctions or template_functions
# method: full low-case letters
# --> templatemethod or template_method
# variable: full low-case letters
# --> templatevariable or template_variable
# constant: full upper-case letters
# --> TEMPLATECONSTANT or TEMPLATE_CONSTANT
# ERROR: ERROR will be suffix
# --> templateerror.ERROR or template_error.ERROR


# difference hierarchy relationship from Java, C#
# --> for Java and C#, namespace > package > class > functions
# --> for Python, namespace > module > package || file > functions
